  "translations": {
    "en": {
      "description": {
        "text": "The rock is a bit chossy in places. The left side is the most appealing, where you can find a few problems in the 5c-7a range.",
        "method": "llm",
        "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
        "sourceIds": [
          "legacy:vinterviken"
        ]
      },
      "sections": {
        "allmant": {
          "title": {
            "text": "General",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:vinterviken"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "The crag is a bit rotten in places. The left side is the finest, where you can find a few problems in the 5c-7a range.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:vinterviken"
            ]
          }
        },
        "vagbeskrivning": {
          "title": {
            "text": "Access",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:vinterviken"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "The crag is a few minutes' walk out on the point from Vintervikens Café (the old Sculpture House) on the right side of the path.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:vinterviken"
            ]
          }
        },
        "leder": {
          "title": {
            "text": "Routes",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:vinterviken"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:vinterviken"
            ]
          }
        },
        "repturer": {
          "title": {
            "text": "Rappels",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:vinterviken"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "Yes, there are a couple of those; one is to the right of the chimney. The fluttery ear, graded 6c, was led as a sport route with a static rope and loops hung from the top. The other is across the bay in a blasting pit, roughly 7a-7b, actually three-star. This one was set up in the same way. These were established about 4-5 years ago.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:vinterviken"
            ]
          }
        }
      },
      "routes": {
        "vinterviken-problem-1": {
          "description": {
            "text": "Do not stand on the scrambling rock at the start.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:vinterviken"
            ]
          }
        },
        "vinterviken-problem-2": {
          "description": {
            "text": "Start SS. Try to do it with as few moves as possible.",
